   1867          /***************************************************************************//**
   1868           * Setup DMA transfer for I2C leader mode non-blocking operations.
   1869           *
   1870           * @details
   1871           *   Configures DMA channels and descriptors specifically for I2C
   1872           *   leader mode non-blocking transfers. It handles leader-initiated write and
   1873           *   read operations to communicate with follower devices on the I2C bus.
   1874           *
   1875           *   Leader mode operations supported:
   1876           *   - Leader write: Send data to follower device
   1877           *   - Leader read: Request and receive data from follower device
   1878           *   - Both 7-bit and 10-bit follower addressing
   1879           *
   1880           * @param[in] i2c_handle Pointer to the I2C handle structure containing:
   1881           *                       - I2C peripheral instance (must be in leader mode)
   1882           *                       - Transfer direction (SL_I2C_WRITE or SL_I2C_READ)
   1883           *                       - Follower address (7-bit or 10-bit)
   1884           *                       - Buffer information (TX/RX buffers and lengths)
   1885           *                       - DMA channel allocation
